The President's Commission on White House Fellows has announced the appointment of the 2022-2023 class of White House Fellows. The program, founded in 1964, offers young leaders the opportunity to work at the highest levels of the Federal government for a year. Fellows work with senior White House Staff, Cabinet Secretaries, and other top-ranking Administration officials, gaining valuable experience and leadership skills. The Fellows come from diverse backgrounds and professions, including the private sector, local government, academia, non-profit sector, medicine, law, and the armed forces. The application process for the 2023-2024 Fellowship year will open on November 1, 2022.